      <h2 id="google-ads-basics">Google Ads for HVAC: The Fundamentals</h2>
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg">
        <p>HVAC Google Ads differ fundamentally from retail or e-commerce campaigns. Your customers are typically in crisis mode (broken AC in July heat) or making major purchasing decisions (new HVAC system). This creates unique opportunities and challenges that require specialized approaches.</p>

        <p>The HVAC customer journey breaks into three distinct phases: emergency repair (immediate need), preventive maintenance (planning ahead), and system replacement (major investment). Each requires different ad messaging, landing pages, and budget allocation strategies.</p>

        <p>Emergency repair searches convert at 12-18% (industry average is 3-5%), but competition is fierce. Installation searches have longer sales cycles but higher average order values. Maintenance searches convert at lower rates but create recurring revenue opportunities.</p>
      </div>

      <h3>HVAC Ad Types That Work</h3>

      <div class="prose prose-lg">
        <p>Search ads dominate HVAC marketing, capturing 78% of successful campaign budgets. Emergency repair ads ("AC not working," "furnace won't start") generate immediate calls but cost $25-45 per click in competitive markets.</p>

        <p>Local Service Ads (LSAs) show above traditional search results for verified HVAC contractors. LSAs cost per lead ($30-80 depending on market) rather than per click, making them predictable for budgeting. However, LSAs require Google Guarantee verification and consistent review management.</p>

        <p>Display remarketing ads work well for installation services, targeting visitors who viewed your furnace or AC replacement pages but didn't convert. These campaigns typically cost $2-5 per click with 1-3% conversion rates.</p>
      </div>

