      <div class="prose prose-lg">
        <p>These numbers assume properly optimized campaigns with 12-18% conversion rates for emergency services and 3-5% for installation services. Companies spending below these ranges often struggle to achieve sufficient volume for meaningful optimization.</p>

        <p>Budget allocation should follow the 60-25-15 rule: 60% emergency repair keywords, 25% installation keywords, 15% maintenance and tune-up keywords. Emergency keywords drive immediate revenue but require larger budgets due to higher competition.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 id="keyword-strategies">High-Converting HVAC Keywords</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg">
        <p>HVAC keyword research requires understanding search intent and seasonal patterns. Emergency repair keywords spike during extreme weather, while installation keywords peak during shoulder seasons when customers plan major purchases.</p>

        <p>High-intent emergency keywords include "AC not cooling," "furnace won't turn on," "no heat," and "HVAC repair near me." These keywords cost $20-45 per click but convert at 15-25% rates when properly targeted.</p>

        <p>Installation keywords like "new furnace cost," "AC replacement," and "heat pump installation" have lower click costs ($8-18) but longer sales cycles. These campaigns require nurture sequences and multiple touchpoints before conversion.</p>
      </div>

