      <h2 id="landing-page-essentials">Landing Page Essentials</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg">
        <p>HVAC landing pages must address the emotional state of your visitors. Someone searching "AC not working" at 11 PM in July is panicked, not comparison shopping. Your landing page needs to immediately communicate availability, expertise, and next steps.</p>

        <p>High-converting HVAC landing pages include phone numbers in the header (visible without scrolling), service area maps showing coverage zones, and clear pricing expectations. Emergency service pages should emphasize 24/7 availability and average response times.</p>

        <p>Installation landing pages require different elements: financing options, manufacturer certifications, before/after photos, and customer testimonials. These pages should build trust and demonstrate expertise rather than urgency.</p>
      </div>

      <h3>Landing Page Elements That Convert</h3>

      <div class="prose prose-lg">
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Above-fold phone number:</strong> 40% of HVAC visitors call within 5 minutes of landing</li>
          <li><strong>Service area verification:</strong> "Yes, we service [ZIP code]" increases conversion by 23%</li>
          <li><strong>Response time promises:</strong> "30-minute callback" or "Same-day service" build urgency</li>
          <li><strong>Licensing and insurance badges:</strong> Required for trust in home service industries</li>
          <li><strong>Live chat availability:</strong> Captures leads when phones are busy during peak times</li>
          <li><strong>Financing options:</strong> Essential for installation campaigns over $3,000</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2 id="call-tracking-setup">Call Tracking and Attribution</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg">
        <p>HVAC businesses live and die by phone calls, making call tracking essential for Google Ads success. Without proper attribution, you're flying blind on which keywords and campaigns drive actual customers versus tire-kickers.</p>

        <p>CallRail dominates the HVAC call tracking space with dynamic number insertion, call recording, and Google Ads integration. Their HVAC-specific features include appointment booking integration and service type tagging for different call types.</p>
