      <h2 id="campaign-structure">Campaign Structure and Management</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg">
        <p>Successful HVAC Google Ads accounts use tightly themed ad groups with 5-15 closely related keywords each. Broad keyword groups like "HVAC services" waste budget on irrelevant clicks and make optimization difficult.</p>

        <p>Campaign structure should mirror your service offerings: separate campaigns for emergency repair, installation, maintenance, and specific equipment types (furnaces, heat pumps, ductless systems). This granular approach allows precise budget control and messaging optimization.</p>

        <p>Geographic targeting requires careful consideration of drive time versus profitability. Many HVAC companies make the mistake of targeting their entire metro area instead of focusing on profitable service zones within 45-60 minutes drive time.</p>
      </div>

      <h3>Recommended Campaign Structure</h3>

      <div class="prose prose-lg">
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Emergency Repair Campaign:</strong> 40-50% of total budget, 24/7 scheduling, aggressive bidding</li>
          <li><strong>Installation Campaign:</strong> 30-35% of budget, business hours scheduling, longer conversion tracking</li>
          <li><strong>Maintenance Campaign:</strong> 15-20% of budget, seasonal adjustments, relationship building focus</li>
          <li><strong>Competitor Campaign:</strong> 5-10% of budget, brand protection and conquest targeting</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <h2 id="measuring-success">Measuring ROI and Success Metrics</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg">
        <p>HVAC Google Ads success requires tracking beyond basic clicks and impressions. The metrics that matter are cost per qualified lead, customer acquisition cost, and lifetime value ROI. A $200 cost per lead that generates a $5,000 installation customer represents 25:1 return on ad spend.</p>

        <p>Emergency repair campaigns should target 3-5% conversion rates with $50-150 cost per conversion. Installation campaigns typically see 1-2% conversion rates but $300-800 cost per conversion due to higher value services.</p>

        <p>Tracking revenue attribution requires integrating your <a href="/hvac/crm/best-crm-for-small-hvac-companies">CRM system</a> with Google Ads. ServiceTitan, Jobber, and Housecall Pro all offer Google Ads conversion tracking to connect ad clicks with completed jobs and revenue.</p>
      </div>

