      <h2 id="common-mistakes">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg">
        <p>The biggest HVAC Google Ads mistake is bidding on broad, non-commercial keywords like "air conditioning" or "heating and cooling." These searches generate expensive clicks from people researching rather than ready to hire a contractor.</p>

        <p>Geographic targeting errors waste significant budget. Contractors often target entire metro areas instead of profitable service zones. A Phoenix HVAC company shouldn't bid on clicks from Scottsdale if they charge trip fees for that distance.</p>

        <p>Seasonal budget management failures cost money and opportunities. Many contractors pause ads during slow seasons instead of shifting focus to installation and maintenance services. Year-round presence builds brand awareness and captures early planners.</p>

        <p>Landing page mismatches between ad copy and page content kill conversion rates. An ad promising "24/7 emergency service" that leads to a general services page will have terrible performance compared to a dedicated emergency repair landing page.</p>
      </div>

      <h3>Budget Optimization Mistakes</h3>

      <div class="prose prose-lg">
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Underfunding weekends:</strong> Emergency calls peak on weekends when regular contractors are closed</li>
          <li><strong>Ignoring mobile optimization:</strong> 67% of emergency HVAC searches happen on mobile devices</li>
          <li><strong>Generic ad copy:</strong> "HVAC services" performs 3x worse than "Emergency AC Repair - Same Day Service"</li>
          <li><strong>Poor negative keyword lists:</strong> Blocking irrelevant searches like "DIY" and "how to" saves 15-25% budget</li>
          <li><strong>Set-and-forget campaigns:</strong> Successful HVAC ads require weekly optimization and seasonal adjustments</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

